WORLD; 
SOVIET-JAPAN SPACEFLIGHT DEC. 2 
The Soviet-Japanese spaceflight, which will put a Japanese television 
journalist in orbit, is scheduled for Dec. 2, the Soviet Glavkosmos space 
agency said today. 
The agency said two Japanese candidates for the flight, Kikuchi Rioko and 
Akiyama Toehiro, have completed the first six months of training for the 
mission. 
The TBS Radio &amp; Television Broadcasting Co. of Japan is paying $9 million 
for the first joint Soviet-Japanese launch of one of their journalists to the 
Mir space station. 
